# AppKit naming conventions

New code in this repo follows the naming scheme of the upstream
`databricks/appkit` source. This governs **new** files, packages,
directories, and symbols only - existing files are NOT retroactively
renamed or moved to satisfy this rule.

## Files and directories

- kebab-case for every `.ts` / `.tsx` file and every directory
  (`base-server.ts`, `genie-chat.tsx`, `create-agent.ts`,
  `remote-tunnel-controller.ts`). A single-word name is already
  kebab-case (`chart.ts`, `genie.ts`).
- React component files are kebab-case too (`genie-chat.tsx`,
  `data-table.tsx`), not PascalCase.
- Exceptions AppKit itself keeps: the Vite entry pair `App.tsx` and
  `main.tsx` stay as-is.

### Conventional filenames

- `index.ts` - re-export barrel for a directory.
- `types.ts` - shared types for the surrounding module.
- `defaults.ts` - default config / option values.
- `schemas.ts` - zod (or similar) schemas.
- `policy.ts`, `params.ts`, `helpers.ts` - focused helpers next to
  their owner.
- `use-*.ts` - React hooks (`use-genie-chat.ts`, `use-agent-chat.ts`).
- `*.example.tsx` - example / demo usage of a component.
- `*.generated.ts` - generated output; never hand-edited.
- `*.browser.ts` - browser-only variant of a same-named module.

## Directory grouping by concern

Group files into concern directories rather than a flat folder:

- `plugins/<name>/` - one directory per plugin.
- `connectors/<service>/` - one directory per external service client.
- `core/`, `context/`, `errors/`, `hooks/`, `charts/<type>/`.
- `features/<feature>/{components,hooks,lib}/` - feature-scoped UI.

## Plugin layout

A plugin lives in `plugins/<name>/`:

- `index.ts` re-exports `./<name>` and `./types`.
- `<name>.ts` holds the implementation: a
  `class <Name>Plugin extends Plugin` plus the lowercase factory
  `export const <name> = toPlugin(<Name>Plugin)`.
- Co-locate `defaults.ts`, `types.ts`, `schemas.ts`, etc. as needed.

## Connector layout

A connector lives in `connectors/<service>/` with `client.ts`,
`types.ts`, `defaults.ts`, and `index.ts`.

## Identifiers

- Functions: camelCase. Factory functions take a verb prefix:
  `create*` (`createApp`, `createAgent`), `define*` (`defineTool`),
  `get*` (`getWorkspaceClient`, `getExecutionContext`), `build*`
  (`buildToolkit`).
- Plugin factory functions are lowercase, named after the plugin, and
  produced via `toPlugin(...)`: `export const genie = toPlugin(GeniePlugin)`.
- Classes, interfaces, and types: PascalCase (`GeniePlugin`,
  `AgentDefinition`, `AppKitMcpClient`). Plugin classes are suffixed
  `Plugin`.
- Module-level constants: SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE.

## Packages

Scoped kebab-case package names (`@databricks/appkit`,
`@databricks/appkit-ui`). In this repo that scope is `@dbx-tools/*`.
